<br>
A few points:<br>
 <br>
1) The name of the book is  “Project Orion The True Story Of The Atomic Spaceship’ and it was written by ‘Freeman Dyson’ not  ‘freemon dyson’.  I don’t think there is a person on this board that hasn’t read it except perhaps you. If you had been able to digest the material in Dyson’s book you would have noted that  pusher plate erosion, Plate harmonics, and shock absorption and return compliance were things that the original program members hadn’t been able to completely solve because they were never allowed to conduct any live tests with nuclear warheads and the crude computers and software of that era couldn’t give them satisfactory answers to those problems.<br>
2) I am  sorry  to break it to you but you apparently know NOTHING about explosives. Explosives are not magic and a shaped charge of any kind is designed to direct as much force in a desired  direction as possible but that amount is never 100% that is simply impossible.  There is only one  fool that believes that 100% of an explosion can be directed in a single direction and that is you. I’ll tell you what, make the best ‘Omni Directional charge” that you can envision and then place it on top of your head making sure to direct the blast away from yourself and detonate it. Well with 100% of the force going in one direction you shouldn’t even get a scorch mark on your noggin should you.  <br>
3)    Since  you obviously don’t know I will enlighten you about one type of shaped charge, the hollow cavity charge that is used in  HEAT warheads (HEAT stands for  High Explosive Anti Tank ). In a 120mm M830 HEAT round the projectile weights about 35 pounds most of the mass is actually the heavy steel casing needed to contain the explosion momentarily while the high velocity jet forms and defeats the targets armor. Actually the explosive filler accounts for only about 30% of the warheads total mass. After the jet stream has done its job the casing then shatters into hundreds of fragments that we in the business call shrapnel. The fragments of the casing scatter in an expanding doughnut shaped cloud and the direction of expansion is approximately perpendicular to the high velocity jet stream that defeats the enemy armor . Even with that heavy metal casing only a fraction of the HEAT warheads explosive energy is focused and directed in the desired direction. That doesn’t sound like 100% efficiency to me Tim1965. I have a challenge for you  post a diagram of an explosive  charge that directs 100% of its energy in a single direction. When you do that I’ll post a design for an antigravity drive that runs on hot air. I guess you know who I am going to ask to provide the hot air. <br>
4) You made your lack of knowledge  about explosives and rockets perfectly  clear when you proposed that absurd  ground launched chemically  powered Orion. Your idea was absurd on the face of it.  Tim1965 everyone but you knows that a  regular old chemical rocket engine  is going to get more performance out of a given mass of fuel and oxidizer  than  an equal mass of chemical pulse units that are detonated outside the ship without the benefit of a combustion chamber and nozzle to direct the force in the desired direction. <br>
